A Python program is available to automate the pre-processing steps for the image restoration approach, including input image calibration and normalization, cloud and no-data mask creation, and patch extraction. The program chains together various OTB applications and can be run from the command line.
The deep-gapfill code provides a Python implementation for building and training the deep learning architecture used in the image restoration approach. The code can be downloaded from the Deep-Gapfill repository and includes functions for data loading, model building, and training.